Definitions:

--username=<username> 
	The login username to be used in the username-token for authentication.

[--password=<password>]
	It is an optional argument, corresponding to the password for the given user-name. If not specified, the password will be prompted.

Description:
	This command is used to create a username-token which is added to the calling context. More than one username-token credential cannot be possessed. The whoami command can be used to view the list of credentials. 

